    {
      "id": "dca4a83829dccd5dcb644560f8d8702059e2665d",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2015-06-30 07:15:37.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1\n\nWould be good to have a test for the read-only property being set and cleared. For existing files on the OST they should be readable but return -EROFS on write, append, truncate. The MDS would need to be given 5+ seconds to react before creating new files, since it would still have precreated objects cached. \n\nAlso worthwhile to test if the OST can be unmounted in this state. I suspect that mounting will not work without some fixes. That should be done in a follow-on patch, probably in conjunction with Fan Yong.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "cdad078666ff9bdb7e6c4de26b8629bc070c3dfe",
      "author": {
